Tokens.text: "Interesting," the sheriff says as he takes another look around. He picks up the copy of "Arctic Lightning," and then shakes his head.
"Such a violent movie," he mumbles. "No wonder these kids are like savages."

Tokens.text: "George, you say? I've heard the name before, but never in the same sentence as 'nice'."
"He's crazy," the sheriff says. "Used to get into fights all the time with the other kids, regularly drinks and does drugs...Some lady even claims he strangled her cat with his bare hands."

Tokens.text: You and the sheriff search through the filing cabinets and drawers, eventually scrapping together a small stack of papers.
- Punish and prevent disruptive behavior, with physical force if appropriate.
- Confiscate personal possessions at random times,in order to aggravate subjects.
Notes: Subject shows consistent disobedience and disdain for authority members. Force necessary in multiple situations. Recommended for placement in advanced program.

Treatment continues to proceed as planned. Despite the lack of major developments researchers note behavorial changes in the subjects, most notably an increase in aggression. With luck, a more satisfactory result with be achieved in Phase 2.
- Expose subjects to violent film, in order to desensitize subjects.
- Gradually introduce and normalize the harm of animals to the subjects.
- Introduce regular drug use to subjects; continue with exposure to violent film and animal abuse.
The list appears to be unfinished.

Tokens.text: Notes: Model subject. Complies with treatments with little resistance, almost willingly at times. Difficulty with socialization.
Notes: Highly dangerous to staff and peers. Known to craft and hide weapons from household materials. Has severely injured other subjects on multiple occasions.

During the night, multiple staff were injured in an altercation involving Subject 022 and multiple other subjects. Subject displayed extreme aggression and agitation. The situation has further isolated Subject 022 from his peers.
Note: HQ has requested Subject 002 be observed and considered for potential use in the future.

A fire was started in the facility today. Staff managed to extinguish it, but the perpetrator is unknown. All matches and lighters have been confinscated from subjects. Subjects and staff alike regularly show unease and anxiety.
"Right...But we need to be careful. You head back to the inn and stay low. I'll go to my office and phone this in. Come meet me in an hour."
"You as well, detective. Just what in the hell have we found here...?"
